  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Medicine Ball Countermovement Throw uses the medicine ball to train coordinated dip-and-drive timing and fast full-body projection. The drill is valuable only when the athlete can keep the intended phase quality, safe spacing, and repeatable mechanics.","setup":["Choose a medicine ball that matches the drill intent and athlete size.","Use a solid wall target and stand far enough away that the ball returns safely, if it returns at all.","Clear the lane, wall, floor, or partner space before the first rep.","Explain the finish position and stop command before adding speed."],"execution_steps":["Load hips, trunk, and hands into the starting shape.","Throw the ball with maximal intent while keeping the torso organized.","Catch, recover, or collect the ball safely.","Reset posture before the next attempt."],"coach_cues":["Fast ball.","Brace then throw.","Throw through the target.","Reset between reps."],"common_faults":["Choosing a ball too heavy for speed.","Leaking through the ribs or low back.","Over-rotating after release.","Counting slow, inaccurate throws as good reps."],"breathing_cues":["Breathe in during load.","Exhale sharply on release.","Use calm breaths between attempts."],"quality_gate":["Ball speed, catch quality, or load path stays consistent across the set.","Ribs, pelvis, and spine stay organized without pain.","Athlete can reset safely before the next rep or interval."],"stop_signs":["Pain, dizziness, breath-holding panic, or unsafe ball rebound.","Throw, slam, catch, or footwork quality drops for two consecutive reps.","Partner spacing, wall target, or floor conditions become unsafe."]}'::jsonb,
