  ('medicine-ball-dead-bug-press', 'The ball gives immediate feedback: speed, accuracy, rebound, catch quality, or load path changes when the athlete leaks force. Medicine Ball Dead Bug Press therefore links bracing, timing, and force transfer in a coachable way.', 'Belongs in Prepare & Access because the drill raises activation and positional access without meaningful fatigue. The slot `activate` supports later higher-cost work.', 'Use early in Prepare & Access as a low-fatigue activation drill before harder trunk, throwing, sprint, or lifting work. Keep effort submaximal and breathing controlled.', 'The common mistake is ignoring phase intent and chasing difficulty instead of quality.', 'Scale by lowering load, range, and speed while preserving breath and alignment. Progress only one variable at a time and let the quality gate decide.'),
  ('medicine-ball-hollow-body-hold', 'The ball gives immediate feedback: speed, accuracy, rebound, catch quality, or load path changes when the athlete leaks force. Medicine Ball Hollow Body Hold therefore links bracing, timing, and force transfer in a coachable way.', 'Belongs in Resilience because the drill builds trunk control, braking, catch tolerance, joint ownership, or anti-movement capacity rather than maximal speed or conditioning.', 'Use after access work and after high-speed Output priorities, or as a controlled trunk/braking block before late conditioning. Stop when position, breath, or catch quality breaks.', 'The common mistake is treating control work like max power or conditioning. Keep range, load, and tempo small enough that trunk position and breathing stay clean.', 'Scale by reducing load, range, lever length, catch speed, or set duration before adding complexity. Progress only one variable at a time and let the quality gate decide.'),
