  ('medicine-ball-push-up-hand-switch', 'The ball gives immediate feedback: speed, accuracy, rebound, catch quality, or load path changes when the athlete leaks force. Medicine Ball Push-Up Hand Switch therefore links bracing, timing, and force transfer in a coachable way.', 'Belongs in Capacity because the main adaptation is loaded force production, structural reserve, and tissue tolerance with the slam ball used as the primary resistance.', 'Use in Capacity after Output work and before hard conditioning. Load progressively, rest enough to keep reps strong, and avoid racing the implement.', 'The common mistake is racing awkward-object strength reps or using a ball so heavy that the athlete loses posture, range, or repeatable load path.', 'Scale by reducing ball weight, range, tempo demand, carry distance, or ground-to-shoulder complexity before adding load. Progress only one variable at a time and let the quality gate decide.'),
